      <head>Franz Werfel</head>

      <div>
        <p>Austrian poet and writer, who played an important part in the 20th-century
          Verdi-renaissance, author of <title level="m">Verdi: Roman der Opera</title> (Verdi: Novel
          of the Opera) (Berlin, 1924, 2/1930), which compared Verdi favorably to Wagner, also
          German translator of the libretti of <title level="m">La forza del destino</title>, 
            <title level="m">Simon Boccanegra</title>, and <title level="m">Don Carlos</title>, all highly
            successful, and author of many articles on Verdi.</p>
      </div>
